  "description": "The recent update to X’s Terms of Service is getting a lot of attention, mostly framed as a sudden shift toward AI exploitation or a betrayal of users. What’s actually happening is more specific and more revealing. The new terms don’t represent a fundamental change in what X does; they represent a change in how explicitly the company is willing to describe its relationship to user data, and a tightening of legal control around practices that have existed for most of the platform’s life.\n",
  "name": "2025-12-18, On x's updated terms of service",
